200,000 Croatians Suffer From Depression
ZAGREB , November 29 ( Xinhua ) -- About 200,000 Croatians are suffering from depression , said the latest statistics released by the official daily Vjesnik .
This is mainly a result of alcohol abuse , which can cause mental disorder and psychosis , said an expert of the country 's association of suicide prevention .
Fifteen percent of the depression victims committed suicide .
The population of Croatia is 4.8 million .
